OL,3,C'Diversity is a strength': Sir Sadiq
OL,4,Creacts to Laila Cunningham's burka
OL,5,Ccomments
OL,7,F"Where covering your hair and the
OL,8,Fburka comes is Wahhabism in Saudi. And
OL,9,Fthese are very extreme traditions. In
OL,10,Fthe Middle East, before the extreme
OL,11,FMuslim takeover of it, people were in
OL,12,Fbikinis in Iran and Egypt. It wasn't
OL,13,Flike it is today."
OL,15,F'I would never dream of telling a
OL,16,Fwoman how to dress, nor would I think
OL,17,Fthat's a reason to, arrest them or
OL,18,Fcharge them with anything,' says Sir
OL,19,FSadiq Khan
